The paper focuses on designing maker kits to introduce novice users to complex technologies such as artificial intelligence (AI), which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the principles of approachable design, simplicity, extensibility, and accessibility, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper reports on user interactions with the project on GitHub, which involves data mining (cs.LG).
